  "text": "To compare the properties of the three dermal populations in culture, we isolated P2 dermal cells from mice in which green fluorescent protein (GFP) is expressed under the control of the Sox2 promoter (Sox2eGFP mice; [CITATION_1] . Cells were labeled with anti-CD133 and sorted on the basis of GFP and CD133 expression (Figure 3a ). After cultivation in AmnioMax hydrogels for 2 weeks, AP-positive spheres were formed by all three cell populations, whereas GFP protein was only detected in cultures of CD133 þ GFP þ cells ( Figure 3b) .",
